# ExamSpark UX Architecture Rule

Full spec: [`UX_ARCHITECTURE.md`](UX_ARCHITECTURE.md) · [`PRD.md`](PRD.md)

## Design Process (Mandatory Order)

1. Information Architecture → 2. Navigation Flow → 3. Screen Hierarchy → 4. UI last

Never mock UI before IA is locked.

## UX Goals

- User understands app in **30 seconds**
- **Reduce taps** — workspace tabs, not page stacks
- **Every feature** has one logical primary place
- **No unnecessary screens** — overlays over routes
- Premium AI SaaS feel — not traditional edu-app

## Navigation — 5 Tabs Only

`Home` · `Library` · `Groups` · `Progress` · `Profile` — **nothing more**.

Teacher Dashboard via Profile. Subscription via Profile. Settings via Profile.

## Profile Screen

Rows: Subscription · Credits · Storage · Library Size · Settings · Help · Logout
Teacher only: Teacher Dashboard row

Credits also on Home top bar pill.

## Home = Chat Screen

**Top bar ONLY:** Logo · Search · Credits · Notification · Profile

**Bottom sticky:** Attachment · Record · Text · Send

**After lecture:** Stay in conversation — NO navigate to new screen. Embed Study Tabs + AI Actions below AI response.

## Core Differentiator — Study Workspace

**ChatGPT = conversation only. ExamSpark = conversation + Study Workspace.**

When a lecture opens:
- **Desktop:** tabs on **right panel** (split pane with conversation)
- **Mobile:** tabs in **bottom sheet** (swipe up)

Canonical tabs: Notes · Summary · Transcript · Flashcards · Quiz · Revision · Ask AI

One lecture = all study inside — no page hopping. Same `StudyWorkspace` widget everywhere.

Do not build ChatGPT clone. Build conversation + education workspace.

## Library

Separate tab. Folders · Search · Recent · Favorites → tap card → Study Workspace.

## Groups

WhatsApp **feel**, NOT chat. Teacher broadcast only. Students: read · quiz · Ask AI — no message · no upload.

## Teacher Dashboard

Cards only — Students · Subscribers · Revenue · Credits · Storage · Groups · Analytics. No spreadsheet tables.

## Design

White · black · minimal · premium · fast. Not colorful edu-app. Not ChatGPT clone — Study Workspace is the differentiator.

## Build Order

1. ✅ IA + Screen Hierarchy (`IA_SCREEN_HIERARCHY.md`)
2. Flutter UI (Phase 2 — ask founder) → 3. Polish → 4. DB → 5. Backend

## Code Targets (when implementing)

- `AppShell` — 5-tab bottom nav
- `HomeScreen` — conversation + `BottomInputBar` + `LectureResultCard`
- `StudyWorkspace` — shared widget (replace standalone `NotesResultScreen` pattern)
- `LibraryScreen` · `GroupsScreen` · `TeacherDashboardScreen`

Do not scatter feature buttons on Home. Do not add routes per study tab.
